726515f-b.title: Queens: Dry Harbor Road - 80th Street
726515f-b.text:
Dry Harbor Road, west side, between 84th Street (left) and
80th Street (right) showing in three views an old house of which
the following were the owners: - C. Westlake, 1852; F. Trippe,
1860; J. Treppe, 1873; and F. Kochesberger from 1891-1896. This
house does not appear in the 1929 Queens Atlas.
April 1923
Views 1,2 and 3
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection
MAY BE REPRODUCED.

726502f-a.title: Queens: Dry Harbor Road - Furmanville Avenue
726502f-a.text:
Dry Harbor Road (left not shown) west side, south of Furman-
ville Avenue, showing the old Methodist burying ground and site
of the old Methodist meeting house of 1852. Most of the markers
ave fallen, some are broken, a few of them remain s tanding. One
reads Susanah Calyer died 1839, age 3 years. In the background
the writer believes is 79th Place shoxing houses tbereon looking
south from Furmanville Avenue. The cemetery property is now 1927,
occupied by frame homes. One Burkhard owned it (ceaetery) in 1909.
Arril 1923.
Eumene L. Armbruster Collection
